Revision history for Net-Async-MCP-Run

{{$NEXT}}

  - Command transformation via L<MCP::Run::Compress> (e.g. Co-Authored-By injection)
  - Disable transformation via C<MCP_RUN_COMPRESS_NO_CO_AUTHORED> env var
  - Rename to Net::Async::MCP::Run (was Net::Async::MCP::Server)
  - Now inherits from Net::Async::MCP::Server (the new base server dist)
  - run_stdio method added to Run module

0.001     2026-04-25 13:33:52Z
  - Initial release (as Net::Async::MCP::Server)
  - Async MCP server for command execution
  - Built on IO::Async and Future::AsyncAwait
  - Exposes 'run' tool for command execution
  - Supports allowed_commands whitelist, working_directory, timeout
  - Optional output compression via MCP::Run::Compress
  - Per-command validation via validator coderef